  "texts": [
    "The coverage reports the fraction of simulations in which a 95% nominal confidence interval centered around the plug-in regression coefficient β and the debiased coefficient β debiased cover the target regression coefficient.",
    "For each combination of left hand side variable W r, large language model m and prompting strategy p, we randomly sample 5,000 Congressional bills and calculate the plug-in regression β and bias-corrected coefficient β * with the policy topic as a covariate.",
    "We vary the size of the validation sample over 2.5%, 5%, 10%, 25% and 50%.",
    "Results are averaged over 1,000 simulations.",
    "See Appendix Section D.2 for discussion."
  ],
